{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17641667","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17641667"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T19:30:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T19:30:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17897"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17897","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17897"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10611"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72754"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10611","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10611"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17897"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58224"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"5099"},{"type":"tags","id":"10053"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"24726"},{"type":"contributions","id":"24729"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72754","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72754"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 62-year-old woman presents to the hospital after a prolonged period of fasting due to a self-imposed restrictive diet. She is now being re-fed under medical supervision. During the refeeding process, her metabolism begins to reset.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following metabolic changes does not occur during the refeeding process after fasting?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Suppressed adipose tissue lipolysis","Suppressed hepatic glucose output","Decrease in lipogenesis in adipose tissue","Increased glycogen synthesis in liver","Increased insulin secretion"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDuring refeeding after a period of fasting, the body undergoes several metabolic changes primarily driven by increased insulin secretion. \u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased insulin secretion\u003C/strong\u003E leads to \u003Cstrong\u003Esuppressed adipose tissue lipolysis\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Esuppressed hepatic glucose output\u003C/strong\u003E as the body shifts from a catabolic to an anabolic state.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased glycogen synthesis in the liver\u003C/strong\u003E occurs as glucose becomes more available and insulin promotes glycogen storage.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EContrary to the other changes, there is an \u003Cstrong\u003Eincrease in lipogenesis in adipose tissue\u003C/strong\u003E due to insulin\u0027s anabolic effects, not a decrease. Insulin promotes the storage of energy in the form of fat, so lipogenesis is typically increased during refeeding.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Refeeding after fasting leads to metabolic changes including increased insulin secretion, which suppresses lipolysis and hepatic glucose output.","Refeeding stimulates glycogen synthesis in the liver as glucose becomes more available.","Lipogenesis in adipose tissue typically increases with refeeding due to insulin\u0027s anabolic effects."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Judge A, Dodd MS. Metabolism. Essays Biochem. 2020 Oct 8;64(4):607-647. doi: 10.1042/EBC20190041. PMID: 32830223; PMCID: PMC7545035","Wang Y, Wu R. The Effect of Fasting on Human Metabolism and Psychological Health. Dis Markers. 2022 Jan 5;2022:5653739. doi: 10.1155/2022/5653739. PMID: 35035610; PMCID: PMC8754590","Nakrani MN, Wineland RH, Anjum F. Physiology, Glucose Metabolism. 2023 Jul 17. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32809434","Chandel NS. Lipid Metabolism. Cold Spring Harb Perspect Biol. 2021 Sep 1;13(9):a040576. doi: 10.1101/cshperspect.a040576. PMID: 34470787; PMCID: PMC8411952"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58224"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17897"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"58224","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/58224"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-22T08:12:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-22T08:12:54+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10611"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72754"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"76","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/76"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level II","synonyms":null,"description":"Understand (interpreting and summarizing information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4929","li